<br>
I got: Air pet, earring, mantle and *FIREBOLT OF TALLON* (a dropable version, I put in a petition)<br>
<br>
Info about the air pet...<br>
<br>
Good news: It is probably lvl 60, maybe 59 (red to lvl 57, blue to *edit*61), max hit 83, has around 3750 hps, it seems to take less dmg then the epic while tanking<br>
<br>
Bad news: It stuns via spell cast about as often as the epic pet, It does not appear to be as good as the mage epic.  I parsed some combats with it and compared the same combats I did with the epic on monday.  It appears to do about 50dps against lvl 55 mobs, as does the epic -but- it does not have a proc, and it does not have an innate dmg shield.  <br>
<br>
It hits about dly 17, with muzzle and BO IV.  It was hitting about 57 percent (as does the epic).<br>
<br>
It appears that the air pet, is a striped down epic, that we can equip with procs (summoned items) put a dmg shield on it, and basicaly get to where the epic starts. <br>
<br>
Information about the bauble (abatement earring): It does not appear to work at all.  I ran some tests, yes it glow, but when I cast firebolt of tallon, it cost me 12 percent of my mana with or without the earring.  In contrast If I cast the 59 bolt with the lower lvl earring, w/earring it was 7 percent, w/o it was 8 percent.  It was noticible.  I used the new earring with the 59 bolt, and although it glowed, It was 8 percent with or with out it.<br>
<br>
The abatment earring appears to be broken.<br>
<br>
Btw, if I recall properly the stats for the earring and the shawl (reagent conservation) are identical to the previous versions that went to lvl 60 spells *sigh*<br>
<br>
